  "text": "Another area of interest may be the dynamical evolution of functional brain networks. Indeed, positive feedback is associated with neurological conditions such as epileptic seizures [CITATION_1] . Recently, it has been shown [CITATION_2] that networks derived from fMRI data are better explained by a model where new connections prefer to complete triangles than by traditional preferential attachment. This model is still quite different from our work. It incorporates anatomical distances in its attachment mechanism, but it demonstrates that clustering can play a role in the evolution of real systems.",
